---
description: Combat mechanic rules for simulator code
globs: src/**/*.rs
alwaysApply: false
---
Combat changes must be mechanic-driven.

Rules:
- Preserve the distinction between base stats, additive bonuses, multiplicative bonuses, caps, and final values.
- Never silently merge additive and multiplicative effects.
- Be explicit about combat phases such as round start, on attack, on hit, on crit, round end, death ordering, and proc sequencing.
- Do not replace a general formula with a narrow exception unless the real mechanic is known to be exceptional.
- When changing combat math, state which mechanic the change is intended to model.
- Where possible, keep deterministic calculation boundaries around RNG explicit.
